Job Description:
As one of our Technical Support Analysts you will provide support and advice to IT users resolving technical issues via email, phone and/or in person. You will be responsible for maintaining all network resources including servers, server O/S, database(s) and storage (SAN/NAS/On-premise Cloud Storage - including capacity planning, growth projections, and scalability requirements.)

Typical duties will include:
Installing and configuring computer hardware, software, systems, networks, printers and scanners;
Configuration, installation and maintenance of host servers in a virtual (Hyper-V) environment;
Provision virtual servers and virtual desktops per specifications;
Administration of a virtual IT infrastructure - specialising in Hyper-V;
Support the design set up and maintenance of Citrix environments, including supporting Citrix XenApp 6.x/7.x environments, including build, deployment and maintenance;
Investigating, diagnosing and solving computer software and hardware faults;
Performance of some non-technical duties as required including, but no limited to, answering the telephone, coordinating meetings, entering purchase requisitions, picking up general user queries and helping toward completing jobs/tasks submitted on ticketing system, general documentation;
Contribute to hardware and software improvements within datacentre, on premise and cloud computing environments;
Liaise with other IT personnel and partners for problem resolution;
Maintain security, backup, and redundancy strategies;
Administration and lifecycle management for equipment and software licences;
Assist in (hybrid) cloud planning and design;
Provisioning of virtual computer storage and network resources;
Apache Tomcat installation and administration;
Help designing, deploying and maintaining VoIP server and network devices;
Participation in on-call rota for 24/7/365 requirement to ensure systems, network resources and data availability across all SaaS platforms.
Essential Skills and Experience*
Knowledge of DNS,DHCP,TCP/IP, VLAN, WINS & Active Directory Client Services
General understanding of networking/security technologies (ethernet, routers, switches, firewalls, VPN, etc.);
Design and architecture of datacentre technologies including: datacentre switches, firewall, proxy servers, web filters, load balancers, storage and virtualization from various vendors;
Layer 2/3 technologies and routing protocol experience;
Extensive experience as a Citrix administrator providing operational support and maintenance for Citrix Netscaler, XenDesktop, XenApp and Citrix App-Layering technologies;
MS SQL and Oracle DB experience - installation, configuration and maintenance;
Experience installing and maintaining all Windows OS Desktop and Server;
Experience installing and maintaining Mac OSX;
Ability to independently manage workloads and regularly report back on progress to management.
Skills and experience that will be nice to have: *
A good understanding of:
Direct and Network Attached Storage architectures;
Rain configurations and their benefits;
Core networking technologies and structured infrastructure;
Storage technologies;
Security best practices.
In return for your contribution to the company you will receive 25 days annual leave plus the bank/public holidays, private healthcare, subsidised lunches 4 days a week cooked fresh by our own chef, Phil, and a quarterly bonus scheme.

Our offices are based in the village of Hadlow, Kent, however we will be happy to consider remote working for this role.

